.\" playfield-bcc.1 - Playfield bytecode compiler manpage
.TH PLAYFIELD-BCC 1 "May 2026" "Playfield Engine 1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
playfield-bcc \- compile Ray scripts into bytecode files
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B playfield-bcc
[\fIsourcefiles...\fR]

.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.B playfield-bcc
translates Ray scripts (\fB.ray\fR) into bytecode files
with the extension \fB.raybc\fR.

Each input file is compiled independently. The output file has the same
basename as the input, with its extension replaced by \fB.raybc\fR.
For example, compiling
.I main.ray
produces
.I main.raybc
in the same directory.

.SH EXAMPLES
Compile a single script:
.EX
playfield-bcc main.ray
.EE

Compile multiple scripts:
.EX
playfield-bcc main.ray enemy.ray level.ray
.EE

The above command produces:
.EX
main.raybc enemy.raybc level.raybc
.EE

